<HEADLINE> Zhuhai Promises Uninterrupted Waster Supply for Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHUHAI, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The south China city of Zhuhai
today promised to ensure an uninterrupted water supply for Macao
in spite of facing one of the most critical water shortages in
history.
</P>
<P>
Lei Yulan, deputy secretary of Zhuhai City Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), said today that Zhuhai would spare
no effort to guarantee fresh water supply for Macao.
</P>
<P>
Zhuhai has been in the grips of serious drought over the past
six months, with a sharp drop in water levels in local reservoirs.
</P>
<P>
Weather forecasts indicate that no meaningful rainfall
accumulation is expected in the near future.
</P>
<P>
The city government plans to introduce compulsory water
conservation measures if lack of rain continues over the next few
weeks. Local residents have been encouraged to use water sparingly
in order to ensure Macao's water supply.
</P>
<P>
Zhuhai has supplied water to Macao since the 1960s. Four Zhuhai
reservoirs supply Macao's 150,000 cu.m. daily demand for water.
</P>
<P>
Local officials recently inspected water resources and pledged
that the city will guarantee water quality.
</P>
<P>
Zhuhai has allocated 250 million yuan (30 million US dollars)
to build a pumping station with designed daily water supply
capacity of 1.5 million cubic meters.
</P>
<P>
Relevant departments are monitoring water reserves and are
ready to pipe water from the nearby city of Zhongshan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
