<HEADLINE> Indonesia, Russia Sign Economic Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia and Russia Friday
signed a cooperation agreement in the economic and trade sector
aimed at increasing two-way trade.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian Industry and Trade Minister Rahardi Ramelan said
after signing the agreement with his Russian counterpart Geogry V.
Gabuniya that the agreement covered economic and technical
cooperation and avoidance of double taxation, official Antara News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the two countries would soon establish an
Indonesia-Russia Joint Commission.
</P>
<P>
Ramelan said the two countries would also soon sign other
agreements including agreements on investment guaranty provision,
tourism cooperation and counter-trade as a follow-up to the
medium-and-long-term cooperation accords.
</P>
<P>
The volume of current trade between Indonesia and Russia was
not large, he said. In the January-October period of 1998, two-way
trade reached a total value of 115.4 million U.S. dollars with
Russia enjoying a surplus of 38.4 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
Geogry V. Gabuniya arrived here Friday accompanying Deputy
Prime Minister D. Maslyukov for an official visit to Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Indonesian President B.J. Habibie met with Maslyukov at the
presidential palace in the afternoon, during which both sides
agreed to strengthen bilateral relations in a constructive and
mutual beneficial manner based on the principle of equality.
</P>
</TEXT>
