<DOCNO> XIE19990313.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Khatami's Visit to Italy Produces Economic Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Friday claimed big
economic gains from the ground-breaking visit of President
Mohammad Khatami to Italy, the first ever visit by an Iranian
head of state to Europe since the 1979 Islamic Revolution.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with the official Islamic Republic News Agency,
Minister of Mines and Metals Eshaq Jahangiri said that during
Khatami's visit which concluded Thursday, Tehran and Rome signed
2-billion-U.S.-dollar contracts on projects in Iran.
</P>
<P>
The Italian Ansaldo Energia Company would participate in the
Bandar Abbas power plant project, worth 1 billion dollars, in
southern Iran through the sale of 30 gas turbines and transfer of
technology, he said.
</P>
<P>
Italy will also join in the development scheme of the
250-million-dollar Mobarekeh steel mills, Jahangiri said, adding
the two sides also agreed to establish regular twice-a-week
flights by Italy's national carrier in return for entry permits
for 2,500 Iranian lorries to Italy.
</P>
<P>
Jahangiri also said that the Italian national oil company ENI
will invest up to 3 billion dollars in Iran's oil industry.
</P>
<P>
The two sides signed an agreement backing joint investments,
which will pave the way for mutual investment by public and
private sectors of the two countries, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
