<HEADLINE> Arrested Cigarettes Smuggler to Be Extradited </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Cyprus is extraditing to Germany
a cigarette smuggler arrested in the island in September 1998 at a
request of international police organization Interpol.
</P>
<P>
Hulinsky Richard, 49, is wanted in Germany for importing into
the country cigarettes worth more than 34 million U.S. dollars
without paying duty, the Cyprus News Agency (CNA) reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Three German officers are already on the island to take the
Czech-born Hulinsky back to Germany on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Hulinsky, who has Czech, German and U.S. nationalities, is
also wanted by Czech authorities.
</P>
<P>
He is said to have imported 36 containers of cigarettes from
Cyprus into Germany and the Czech Republic between September 1995
and September 1996, without declaring the goods to pay the
appropriate duty. 
</P>
</TEXT>
