<HEADLINE> Successful Tianjin Import-Export Commodity Fair Closes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The six-day Tenth Tianjin Import-
Export Commodity Fair closed today with the total business volume
of 250 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 businesspeople from a number of countries and
regions attended the fair and clinched deals for wide-ranging
commodities, including clothing, foodstuffs, light industrial
products and machinery.
</P>
<P>
Chinese and foreign businesspeople inked over 100 cooperation,
exchange and development agreements and letters of intent.
</P>
<P>
Dozens of private Chinese companies attended the fair and
participated in import-export trade talks.
</P>
<P>
The Delide Group Co. Ltd., an enterprise recently granted
authority to handle imports and exports internationally, signed a
number of mineral product contracts.
</P>
<P>
The annual fair is jointly sponsored by provinces, autonomous
regions and municipalities in north and northwest China, along
with three national chambers of commerce involved in importing and
exporting textiles, light industrial products, handicrafts,
foodstuffs and livestock by-products. 
</P>
