<DOCNO> XIE19990313.0046 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Addresses Pressing Issues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
said today that China must control its population, protect natural
resources and maintain a sound ecological environment while
gaining economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin, also general secretary of the Central Committee of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), made the remark during an
afternoon work conference on the population, resources and
environment.
</P>
<P>
CPC Central Committee and State leaders including Li Peng, Zhu
Rongji, Li Ruihuan, Hu Jintao, Wei Jianxing and Li Lanqing
attended the meeting held in the Great Hall of the People.
</P>
<P>
"We must always pay close attention to coordinating economic
construction efforts with population control and resource and
environmental protection efforts in order to realize China's cross-
century goals for sustainable economic and social development,"
said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the big population, shortage of resources and
serious environmental pollution have emerged as factors hindering
China's economic and social development.
</P>
<P>
Jiang noted that CPC committees and governments at various
levels have made consistent progress in population control and
resource and environmental protection in accordance with unified
plans adopted by the CPC Central Committee and State Council.
</P>
<P>
"We still face an arduous task in dealing with these issues,"
said Jiang. "We must gain a deep understanding and deal correctly
with the relationship between economic development and population
control, resources and environment from a strategic point of view.
</P>
<P>
"We must fully understand that the urgent task is directly
related to the subsistence and development of the Chinese nation,
and must consistently carry out related work."
</P>
<P>
The president urged local governments to extend greater efforts
to achieve marked results, and stressed that population control
and resource and environmental protection is interrelated and
systematic work which requires coordination between all
departments and society as a whole.
</P>
<P>
He said local officials should conduct research, draft plans
and supervise work instead of simply relying on documents.
</P>
<P>
Officials should conduct on-the-spot examinations, and should
learn the truth by maintaining close contact with grassroots units.
Good experiences should be summarized and popularized, and
solutions should be promptly found to solve problems, according to
Jiang.
</P>
<P>
Those who neglect their duties must be punished, the president
added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
