<DOCNO> XIE19990313.0047 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese President Calls for Improved Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today called for major progress in environmental improvement
efforts during 1999.
</P>
<P>
Jiang made the call during an afternoon meeting covering
population control and resources and environmental protection,
factors crucial to the government's strategy for a sustainable
development of the country.
</P>
<P>
He said governments at all levels should grasp every
opportunity to adjust their industrial structures and strengthen
infrastructure construction in order to enhance environmental
protection efforts.
</P>
<P>
China is striving to halt pollution and ecological
deterioration, and improve the environmental quality of major
cities and regions by the year 2000, with long-term effort to
focus on significantly improving urban and rural environmental
quality by 2010.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said all provinces, autonomous regions and municipalities
should not only control the total discharge volume of pollutants
according to state standards, but should also ensure that all
industries meet discharge standards and all major cities meet
environmental quality standards by 2000.
</P>
<P>
This year is very important for the efforts to achieve the
nation's environmental protection goals in the next century, said
Jiang, adding that environmental policies should be strictly
implemented in all regions, cities and enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He urged the national capital Beijing to further enhance
pollution control efforts and improve its environmental quality
during the year.
</P>
<P>
Jiang said that a national program on ecological and
environmental protection should be drafted and implemented
immediately. Different measures should be adopted in line with
different situations at localities, he added.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19990313.0048 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-03-13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls for Strengthened Family Planning Work </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin
today called for strengthened family planning work to curb China's
population growth.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at an afternoon work conference on population control
and resource and environmental protection, Jiang said population
control deals with a wide range of difficult issues and must not
be relaxed.
</P>
<P>
Jiang, who also serves as general secretary of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, pointed out that China
should further improve its population macro-control, family
planning management and social insurance systems in accordance
with the development needs of socialist market economy.
</P>
<P>
Education, legal, economic and administrative measures should
be adopted to ensure effective population control work. Long-term
efforts should center on controlling the nation's population
growth in line with well established goals, said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He pointed to the difficulties involving population control in
rural areas, and noted that experience shows that the key to the
problem lies in the establishment of grass roots organizations in
the countryside. Specialized personnel should be assigned to
direct the work, funds should be allocated and related regulations
should be adopted, according to Jiang.
</P>
<P>
He added that population control should be directly linked with
economic development and helping farmers gain prosperity. Jiang
said policies should be introduced to help farmers solve problems
related to daily life and production and encourage them to
participate in family planning. 
</P>
</TEXT>
