<BODY>
<HEADLINE> National Cotton Market to Open in Xinjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- A national cotton market will be
put into operation this year in Urumqi, the capital of the
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
The whole project costs some 200 million yuan and the market
has a floor-space of 46,000 sq.m. Its main part has been completed.
</P>
<P>
Xinjiang is the largest cotton producer in China. Last year,
the autonomous region had 980,000 ha. of cotton fields, about one
third of the country's total, and turned out 1.37 million tons,
accounting for six percent of the world's total.
</P>
<P>
Abdul'ahat Abdurixit, chairman of the regional government and a
deputy to the Ninth National People's Congress which is now in its
second annual session here, said Xinjiang plans to realize
industrial management of cotton production by setting up
enterprise groups embracing the functions of production, marketing
and processing, in order to build up an efficient cotton
circulation system.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the cotton market will help reduce the
cost of cotton production and explore the international market.
</P>
<P>
Currently, there is a national cotton trading center in
Zhengzhou, the capital of central Henan Province, also a major
cotton producer in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
