<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Two wanted criminals suspected of
robbing passengers on the Beijing-Moscow international trains
between 1992-1993 were repatriated from Ukraine today with the
help of Interpol, according to China's Ministry of Public Security.
</P>
<P>
The two men -- Bai Huijun and Zhong Jiquan -- allegedly
conducted a series of robberies and rapes on international trains
running from Beijing to Moscow six years ago.
</P>
