<HEADLINE> Bergstrom Wins Men's 30k Cross-Country </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Anders Bergstrom won
his first ever World Cup on Saturday in a men's 30-kilometer
classic cross-country event in Falun, Sweden.
</P>
<P>
Bergstrom, 30, was timed one hour 17 minutes and 3.6 seconds to
edge out Austria's Mikhail Botwinov to the second place by 5.9
seconds.
</P>
<P>
Finn Mika Myllyla, who won three titles at the recent world
championships in Ramsau, Austria, took the third place with 18.3
seconds behind the winner.
</P>
<P>
Norway's king of the track, Bjorn Daehlie, finished a poor
sixth after the seven-time Olympic champion already won his fifth
overall title coming into Saturday's race. 
</P>
