<HEADLINE> Olympic Champion Compagnoni Retires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Olympic gold medallist Deborah
Compagnoni of Italy announced her retirement from Alpine skiing on
Saturday after the final women's race of the 1999 season in Sierra
Nevada, Spain.
</P>
<P>
Compagnoni, Olympic Super-G champion in 1992 and giant slalom
gold winner in 1994 and 1998, said she had planned to retire at
the time one year ago.
</P>
<P>
The three-time world champion won her first world crown in
giant slalom in the 1996 championships here.
</P>
<P>
She won at home in Sestriere in 1997 a double in giant slalom
and slalom. 
</P>
