<HEADLINE> Army-worms Cause Heavy Loses in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Tanzania is now invaded by
hordes of army-worms which have devastated hundreds of acres of
crops in many parts throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
A source from the Ministry of Agriculture and Cooperatives,
according to Saturday's Daily Mail, has said the outbreak of
army-worms in central Morogoro and Dodoma, southern Iringa and
Mbeya regions have caused extensive damages.
</P>
<P>
However, he said local governments have taken steps to destroy
the worms and there should be no fear among the farmers in the
affected regions for famine.
</P>
<P>
"From available records, the outbreak of army-worms is very
much related to the rain seasons," he said, adding "The worms
appear anytime when the short rains are scanty and the long rains
are delayed."
</P>
<P>
Army-worms have destroyed an estimated 500 acres of crop in
Dodoma Region, but the situation is under control as the
authorities have provided more than 700 liters of pesticide to
farmers.  
</P>
</TEXT>
