<HEADLINE> China to Focus on Environmental Problems (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- State Environmental Protection
Administration Director Xie Zhenhua said here today that China
will focus this year's efforts on tackling environmental problems
affecting national economic growth and human health.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a national environmental protection work conference
which opened this morning in the Chinese capital, Xie said major
efforts will center on controlling emissions, in addition to
ensuring that all industries meet discharge standards and all
major cities meet environmental quality standards.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that local environmental departments should strive
to improve environmental quality levels in major cities, river
valleys and coastal areas. Related departments should work
diligently to protect their respective ecological environments in
order to guarantee the safety and overall quality of the nation's
environment.
</P>
<P>
Local governments are responsible for controlling emissions and
should enhance supervision and inspection to ensure enterprises
meet discharge standards, Xie told the meeting, which drew leading
officials from local environmental departments throughout the
country.
</P>
<P>
The director said new projects likely to create pollution
problems should not be approved and obsolete production facilities
and methods should be eliminated.
</P>
<P>
He urged local governments to close small enterprises creating
serious pollution problems and vigorously promote the use of clean
production methods for all industries.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
