<HEADLINE> Estrada Designates Vice President as Govt Caretaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Philippines President Joseph
Estrada has designated Vice President Gloria Macapaga-Arroyo as
government caretaker for the duration of his five-day stay in New
York to attend his eldest brother's burial.
</P>
<P>
Estrada, in a letter to the vice president dated March 11, said
he has convened the Office of the President-Executive Committee
(OP-Execom) to assist her in the discharge of her functions as
caretaker.
</P>
<P>
"It is my privilege to designate you to act for and on my
behalf during my absence, effective upon my departure on Saturday,
March 13, 1999, for the United States, until my return from there
on March 18, 1999," he said.
</P>
<P>
Chaired by Executive Secretary Ronaldo Zamora, the OP-Execom
was created by Estrada last year to monitor developments and
recommend actions to the president on critical national issues
while he is abroad.
</P>
<P>
Estrada said he has ordered other officials, departments and
agencies of the government to extend to the vice president their
"full support and cooperation" during his absence.
</P>
<P>
Estrada is scheduled to leave Saturday night for New York to
attend the burial of his brother Emilio Ejercito Jr., who
succumbed to leukemia on March 11 at the age of 70. 
</P>
</TEXT>
