<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fewer Drug Abusers Reported in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The number of drug abusers
reported to Hong Kong Central Registry of Drug Abuse (CRDA) last
year dropped by 4.1 percent to 16,912 from 17,633 in 1997, a
continuous fall since 1994.
</P>
<P>
This was released by CRDA statistics presented to the Action
Committee Against Narcotics (ACAN) today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at ACAN's quarterly meeting, Commissioner for
Narcotics Clarie Lo said that young drug abusers reported in 1998
had also decreased by 10.9 percent from 1997.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,805 drug abusers under age 21 were reported in
1998 as compared with 3,149 in 1997. These young people
constituted 16.6 percent of the total reported drug abusers in
1998, according to Lo.
</P>
<P>
Newly reported drug abusers also decreased by 6.8 percent, the
official said, adding that the latest statistics also registered a
slight decrease in the number of reported female drug abusers.
</P>
</TEXT>
