<HEADLINE> Manila to Adopt "Growth-With-Equity" Strategy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 13 (Xinhua) - The Philippine government is
adopting a "growth-with-equity" strategy under its medium-term
development plan to ensure that poor Filipinos enjoy the full
benefits of the government's program to pump prime the economy and
implement market-friendly reforms.
</P>
<P>
President Joseph Estrada said this strategy does not involve
"quick-fix" solutions with only short-term gains but a six-year
program that will ensure sustained economic growth and lasting
benefits for the masses even beyond his administration.
</P>
<P>
The government is now conducting multisectoral consultations to
gather feedback and inform the public about its vision and
programs embodied in this medium-term plan.
</P>
<P>
"Our medium-term development plan is from 1999 to 2004. That's
already planned. That's why we cannot solve the problems ailing
the poor outright. The funds for pro-poor programs will have to be
appropriated by Congress, and implemented by the Department of
Budget and Management," he said Saturday on his weekly radio-TV
program.
</P>
<P>
The president said this growth-with-equity strategy is the
reason why his administration is focusing on the modernization of
the agriculture sector and the implementation of labor-intensive
infrastructure projects in the countryside. 
</P>
</TEXT>
