<HEADLINE> Aamodt Boosts Chance after Slalom First Leg </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Norwegian Kjetil Aamodt boosted
his chance for the overall World Cup title after he finished
second in the final men's slalom of the Alpine ski season on
Saturday in Sierra Nevada, Spain.
</P>
<P>
Aamodt, who is trailing overall leader Lasse Kjus of Norway by
92 points currently, finished 0.34 seconds behind Italian leader
Giorgio Rocca, with Kjus a distant 13th.
</P>
<P>
The defending champion Hermann Maier of Austria finished 22nd
and last in Saturday's race, which he seldom competes in, leaving
no hope for retaining his championship.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Austrian Thomas Stangassinger was almost for sure to
win the slalom title as his strong rival, Slovenian Jure Kosir,
made a mistake and finished 19th.
</P>
<P>
The Austrian occupies the leading place in the slalom standings,
75 points ahead of Kosir. 
</P>
</TEXT>
