<HEADLINE> Italian Defense Minister to Visit Egypt Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Italian Defense Minister Carlo
Scognamiglio is due to arrive in Cairo on Monday for a four-day
visit, Italian ambassador to Egypt said on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Scognamiglio is to hold talks with his
Egyptian counterpart Hussein Tantawi on means of boosting military
cooperation, Ambassador Francesco Aloisi De Larderel was quoted by
Egypt's Middle East News Agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
The military ties between Italy and Egypt "is currently
witnessing tangible progress," especially in the exchange of
visits by senior military officials and in holding joint exercises.
</P>
<P>
Italy joined Egypt and France in 1996 to stage naval manoeuvres
every two years.
</P>
<P>
Italy has also pledged to support Egypt's efforts to remove
land mines from the area of Alamein on the Mediterranean coast
under a memorandum of understanding between the two countries, the
Italian diplomat said.
</P>
<P>
Millions of land mines placed during the World War II remain
buried in the Alamein area, posing threats to people's life and
hindering development projects in the area.
</P>
<P>
Egypt has called on the belligerent countries of the battles in
northern Egypt during the World War II to offer funds and
equipment for the removal of the land mines.
</P>
<P>
Tantawi paid a visit to Italy a year ago and signed a memo of
understanding on promoting bilateral cooperation and joint
activities in the military domain, the Middle East News Agency
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
