<HEADLINE> Guangdong's Industrial Output Value Tops China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong Province, the southern
China economic powerhouse, topped other provinces of the country
in terms of industrial output value in December last year,
according to the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The latest figures offered by the bureau show that Guangdong's
industrial output value in December was 92.2 billion yuan (11
billion U.S. dollars), up 19 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
Following Guangdong are Jiangsu Province, with an industrial
output value of 77 billion yuan, and Shanghai Municipality with 55
billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The total industrial output value of the country stood at 596
billion yuan that month, an increase of 14.1 percent on an annual
basis.
</P>
<P>
A close neighbor of Hong Kong, Guangdong is the first province
in the country that opens to the outside world. The province has
developed a high level of processing industry and a large
proportion of its enterprises are export-oriented.
</P>
<P>
South China's Hainan Province had the country's highest monthly
growth rate of 24.5 percent, with its industrial output value
hitting 2.03 billion yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
