<HEADLINE> Citizens in Shenzhen Earn Most in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The people in the southern China
city of Shenzhen continued to enjoy the highest payment among 35
major Chinese cities, according to the National Bureau of
Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Statistics offered by the bureau show that the per capita
monthly income in China's southern boomtown Shenzhen hit 1,479
yuan in November last year, and the per capita monthly disposable
income reached 1,463 yuan while the city's per capita monthly
living expenditure stood high at 1,213 yuan.
</P>
<P>
The city was followed by Guangzhou and Xiamen in per capita
monthly income and disposable income. The monthly per capita
income in Guangzhou was 901 yuan and that of Xiamen, city of
coastal Fujian Province, stood at 741 yuan, in November last year.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen, neighboring Hong Kong, is China's first special
economic zone.  
</P>
