<HEADLINE> Manila Stresses Global Approach to Sustainable Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 13 (Xinhua) - A top Philippine official has cited
the urgency of a global approach to the implementation of
sustainable development as a way for economies to pursue rapid
growth without compromising the ability of future generations to
meet their needs.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a recent regional conference in Manila on
sustainable development, Secretary Antonio Cerilles of the
Department of Environment and Natural Resources said the issue of
ecological onslaught spans across national borders "and it is only
through international cooperation can we stand a chance of solving
it."
</P>
<P>
Cerilles recalled that the Rio de Janiero Conference or the
"Earth Summit" held in Brazil seven years ago "called on all
nations of the world to adhere to the principle of sustainable
development in managing natural resources in a manner that meets
the needs of the present without compromising the ability of
future generations to meet their own needs.
</P>
<P>
"The legal world must be educated on the precarious state of
our environment today, so that it can react and do what must be
done," he said at the Southeast Asian Justices' Symposium on the
Law of Sustainable Development, held recently at the Manila Hotel.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
