<HEADLINE> China's Steel Production on Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- China witnessed growing steel
production last year with the output increasing 6.9 percent from
the previous year to 114.3 million tons, according to the National
Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The output of steel products in 1998 amounted to 105 million
tons, up 9.8 percent on an annual basis, the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the output of light rails plunged 37
percent to 137,200 tons, and that of large rolled steel went down
by 21 percent to 1.03 million tons.
</P>
<P>
Production of pig iron grew by 6.7 percent to 118.6 million
tons last year.
</P>
<P>
The year 1998 also saw an increase in the output of non-ferrous
metals. The output of aluminium oxide hit 3.3 million tons, up 12.
7 percent, and that of aluminium products 1.47 million tons, up 10.
0 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the production of ferro alloys dropped 4.9 percent
to 3.5 million tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
