<HEADLINE> Japan Continues to Be China's Largest Tourist Source </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Tourist arrivals in China from
Japan outnumbered those from other countries in the January-
November period of 1998 despite the Asian financial crisis,
according to figures released by the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
In the first 11 months last year, the number of Japanese
tourists to China reached 1.446 million, and that of total foreign
tourists amounted to 6.529 million.
</P>
<P>
Following Japan are Russia and the United States. Some 640,300
Russian tourists visited China during that period and 629,200
people from the United States toured China.
</P>
<P>
Businessmen and administrative and managerial personnel
accounted for the bulk of the tourists from the three nations,
according to the bureau.  
</P>
