<HEADLINE> Knicks Whipped by Bulls to Tie Lowest Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The New York Knicks tied an
NBA record for fewest field goals in a game, producing just 19 in
a 76-63 loss to the Chicago Bulls on Friday.
</P>
<P>
With the absence of injured Patrick Ewing, New York finished
with lowest point total of all time of 54 set by Utah against the
Bulls in Game 3 of last June's NBA finals.
</P>
<P>
They entered the final quarter trailing 63-33 but were able to
pad their total in the final minutes against Chicago's reserves.
</P>
<P>
The Bulls went on an 18-0 run in the first quarter, and with
their 18-5 advantage in the second led 47-22 at the half behind 20
points from Toni Kukoc, who finished 25.
</P>
<P>
In Indianapolis, Antonio Davis scored seven points in a
decisive 15-5 run that helped Indiana Pacers past Milwaukee Bucks
109-104 in a matchup between the Central Division leaders.
</P>
<P>
Glenn Robinson led Milwaukee with 30 points and Reggie Miller
had 22 for Indiana. Both teams had six players in double figures,
and Indiana shot a season-high 60 percent to snap Milwaukee's six-
game winning streak.
</P>
<P>
In Philadelphia, Allen Iverson, after getting a reprimand from
his teammates for missing practice, had five of his 28 points in
overtime as Philadelphia 76ers surged to win over New Jersey Nets
100-93.
</P>
<P>
Keith Van Horn led the Nets with 25 points and 16 rebounds, but
had only three points in the fourth quarter and no field goals in
the last 20 minutes of the game.
</P>
<P>
In Washington, David Wesley scored a season-high 23 points on 9-
for-15 shooting and Eddie Jones, acquired two days earlier in
major trade with the Lakers, scored eight of his 14 points in the
third quarter as Charlotte Hornets beat Washington Wizards 92-83.
</P>
<P>
In Michigan, Grant Hill scored 13 of his 33 points in the
fourth quarter to lead Detroit Pistons over Boston Celtics 93-83.
</P>
<P>
In Phoenix, Sean Elliott hit a 21-foot jumper at the buzzer as
San Antonio withstood a furious fourth-quarter rally to edge
Phoenix 99-97.
</P>
<P>
In Portland, Oregon, Karl Malone had 21 points and nine
rebounds as Utah Jazz routed Portland Blazers 91-77 for its first
loss in 10 home games.
</P>
<P>
In California, Glen Rice scored 21 points in his Los Angeles
debut as the Lakers defeated Golden State 89-78 for their 10th
straight victory.
</P>
<P>
In Sacramento, Kevin Garnett had 26 points and 17 rebounds as
Minnesota knocked off Sacramento Kings 101-95 even though Terrell
Brandon was absent from the game. 
</P>
