<HEADLINE> China's Locomotive, Rolling Stock Production Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- China saw drops in the production
of locomotives and railway rolling stocks in 1998, according to
figures released by the National Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
The country manufactured locomotives with a total capacity of 2.
8 million kw last year, down 3.5 percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The output of railway passenger coaches last year was 1,580,
down 35.7 percent, and that of railway freight wagons amounted to
23,505, a fall of 22.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
China's railway sector has been confronted with fierce
competition from other sectors of communications industry these
years. 
