<HEADLINE> Shanghai Limiting Number Of Permanent Residents </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 13 (Xinhua) -- The city of Shanghai wants to
hold the number of permanent residents at 14.85 million by the end
of the century.
</P>
<P>
The city's 1999 population and family planning program calls
for 88,000 new babies this year and a natural population growth
rate of minus 0.8 per thousand.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, the number of registered permanent residents will be
held below 13.16 million.
</P>
<P>
Attention will be focused on improving life in the city and the
aging population problem, according to Zhou Jianping, the
municipal family planning commission's Party Secretary.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai has listed 20 medical facilities for the elderly as
one of its 10 major projects for 1999. The number of hospital beds
for the elderly will be increased from the present 2,700 to 4,000.
</P>
