<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil's Palmeiras Draw Olimpia of Paraguay </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JENAIRO, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Dezotti scored a late goal
to give Olimpia of Paraguay a 1-1 draw against group leaders
Brazil's Palmeiras in the Libertadores Cup in Sao Paulo on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Three minutes from time, Palmeiras goalie Velloso failed to
stop Dezotti from lifting a cross into the net, squandering its
lead after Paulo Nunes scored after 58 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The error was the only one Tavarelli made all night as he kept
the first half goalless by palming away Nunes' flick after seven
minutes and later parry Arce's curling free-kick.
</P>
<P>
Olimpia had its best first-half chance on 41 minutes when
Mauricio Paredes side-footed past the post with only goalie
Velloso to beat.
</P>
<P>
The draw kept Palmeiras at the top of group 3 with seven points.
Olimpia move into second with four. Corinthians and Cerro have
three each.
</P>
<P>
The top three in the group after the first stage advance to the
next one. 
</P>
</TEXT>
