in failure to reach 10,000 points after the index hit 9,935.46 in
the previous session.
</P>
<P>
 The Dow closed at 9,876.35, down 21.09. The index had come
within 42 points of 10,000 in early session before pulling back.
(US-Wall Street-Closing)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CARACAS -- Venezuela's crudes basket price closed the week
Friday at 9.91 dollars per barrel, 1.06 dollars above that of last
week, the Energy and Mines Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
The rising trend in oil prices, which started on March 2, is
seen as a favorable reaction to the cold wave hitting the United
States, which has resulted in a bigger volume of purchases, mainly
of fuels for heating. (Venezuela-Oil Price-Rise)
</P>
