series of strict measures to raise revenues with new taxes and to
ensure that the wealthy pay their taxes in a bid to relieve the
country's worst financial crisis in decades.
</P>
<P>
The announcement came after the board of directors of Ecuador'
s Central Bank resigned Thursday as a nationwide strike protesting
the government's economic policies entered the second day. (
Ecuador-Austerity Measures)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Mexican Energy Minister Luis Tellez said Friday
the new oil output cut agreed on with Saudi Arabia, Iran, Algeria
and Venezuela of more than two million barrels a day will
stabilize the world market and slightly raise the price.
</P>
<P>
The ministers of energy of the five major oil producing
countries agreed at a meeting held in The Hague to reduce by two
million barrels a day their daily crude output starting April 1.
(Mexico-Oil-Output cut)
</P>
<P>
