Philippine Central Bank should provide room for further monetary
expansion to achieve at least a 2.6-percent growth in gross
domestic product this year, a local newspaper reported Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Medalla was quoted by Philippine Daily Inquirer as saying that
the attainment of the growth target would largely depend on
whether loan growth would pick up to stimulate more economic
activities. (Philippines-Money Policy) 
