<HEADLINE> Polish president to visit Vietnam Next Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 13 (Xinhua) -- Polish President Aleksander
Kwasniewski will pay an official visit to Vietnam from March
17-20, it was officially announced here Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski, the first Polish head of state to visit Vietnam in
40 years, is making the journey at the invitation of Vietnamese
President Tran Duc Luong.
</P>
<P>
Kwasniewski's upcoming visit aims to consolidate and develop
the traditional friendship and cooperation between the two
countries, enhance mutual understanding, boost trade and
investment, and create conditions for expanding outlets for Polish
goods in Vietnam, according to official report.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam and Poland established diplomatic relations in 1950.
</P>
<P>
During a visit to Poland by former prime minister Vo Van Kiet
in 1997, the two countries agreed to promote multi-cooperation in
transport and communications, minerals, food processing and
trading. Two-way trade is estimated at 80-100 million U.S. dollars
a year.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam exports garments, leather, handicrafts and agricultural
produce to Poland, and imports medicine, powdered milk and
equipment for the coal, steel and ship-building industries from
that country.
</P>
<P>
Poland has loaned Vietnam 70 million U.S. dollars to develop
its ship-building industry and restore historical and cultural
sites.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam has some 300 students and researchers currently
studying in Poland. 
</P>
</TEXT>
