<HEADLINE> China Bans Import of Dutch Poultry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 13 (Xinhua) -- China has stopped importing birds
and poultry from the Netherlands, where there was an outbreak of
Newcastle disease last December, to prevent the serious bird flu
threatening Chinese poultry farms.
</P>
<P>
China suspended the import of birds, poultry and related
products from the Netherlands as of February 23, according to a
notice released recently by the State Administration for Entry-
Exit Inspection and Quarantine.
</P>
<P>
Birds, poultry and related products which came from that
country should be returned or destroyed, according to the notice.
</P>
<P>
The notice said all birds, poultry and related products brought
in by travelers or via mail from that country will be confiscated
and destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Birds, poultry and their products carried by ships, aircraft or
trains coming from that country and traveling through or staying
for a period in China will be quarantined for safekeeping.
</P>
<P>
Seized birds, poultry and products smuggled in from that
country will be destroyed under the supervision of nearby
quarantine departments, the notice said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
