<HEADLINE> Albania FM: Ethnic Albanians to Sign Accord Before Monday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Foreign Minister Paskal
Milo said Friday he believed the Kosovo ethnic Albanians will sign
the peace agreement with Serb negotiators before the Kosovo peace
talks resume Monday in Paris.
</P>
<P>
Milo told his visiting Bulgarian counterpart Nadezhda
Mikhailova that the Kosovo Liberation Army (KLA) is carefully
studying procedural issues for the signing of the agreement and
that he understood the ethnic Albanian delegation would sign the
deal before flying to Paris for talks with the Serb delegation.
</P>
<P>
Milo also warned that Belgrade would face all consequences if
it failed to ink the agreement before the Paris peace talks ended.
</P>
<P>
Albanian Prime Minister Pandeli Majko told Mikhailova during a
meeting on Friday  that Albania is urging the ethnic Albanians to
accept the deal and is hopeful the ethnic Albanian delegation
would do so.
</P>
<P>
Mikhailova promised that her country supports greater autonomy
for the southern Serbian province of Kosovo and believes that it
is necessary for an international force to enter Kosovo to
guarantee the implementation of the peace agreement.
</P>
<P>
Under strong international pressure, the Serbs and the ethnic
Albanians have accepted an autonomy deal for Kosovo that was
hammered out during 17 days of negotiations at the French chateau
of Rambouillet last month.
</P>
<P>
However, neither the Serbs nor the ethnic Albanians have yet
signed the deal. Belgrade also rejected the deployment of NATO
troops in Kosovo to secure peace. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
