<HEADLINE> Posch, Bozzetto Take Final Slalom Titles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Marion Posch of Italy beat defending
champion Karine Ruby of France in the semifinal en route to
winning the Snowboard World Cup women's slalom title in Valdaora
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Posch, the 1999 world champion of the speciality, later edged
out another French opponent Isabelle Blanc in the final.
</P>
<P>
Ruby finished third, ahead of Germany's Heidi Renoth.
</P>
<P>
France's Matthieu Bozzetto, who had secured the men's World Cup
parallel slalom title, beat Germany's Mathias Behounek in the
season's final race.
</P>
<P>
Austrian Stefan Kaltschuetz beat France's Maxence Idesheim for
third place.
</P>
<P>
Defending World Cup champion Richard Richardsson of Sweden
finished a distant 12th in the event.
</P>
<P>
Bozzetto, winner of Thursday's giant slalom, led the final
slalom standings with 5,850 points, ahead of compatriots Mathieu
Chiquet and Nicolas Huet.
</P>
<P>
Following her fourth victory in nine events this season, Posch
commanded the women's standings with 5,500 points. Ruby placed
second with 5,250 and Austria's Manuela Riegler third with 4,750.
</P>
<P>
The World Cup finals continue Saturday with the halfpipe events.
</P>
