<HEADLINE> Fourth Round of Mexico-EU Talks to be Held in Mexico </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The Mexican Foreign Ministry
announced Friday that Mexico will hold the fourth round of talks
with EU here in mid April.
</P>
<P>
A foreign ministry communique said that during the third round
Mexico-EU talks, which ended in Brussels on the same day,
delegates analyzed the access to markets, the rules of product
origin, technical standards, government acquisitions and services.
</P>
<P>
Also discussed at the talks were tariff reduction, movements of
capital, copyrights, international commercial practices, and the
resolution of disputes.
</P>
<P>
The EU is anxious to reach a trade agreement with Mexico. Since
Mexico joined the North American Free Trade Agreement (NAFTA) in
1994 with the United States and Canada, EU trade with Mexico has
dropped by half. Mexico's access to the EU market has also fallen.
</P>
