be held in Beijing, Tianjin, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Shenzhen
between March 13-28.
</P>
<P>
During the exhibition, over 100 colleges and universities in 16
countries will brief Chinese students and their parents on the
situation of higher education in their respective countries, the
policies toward the Chinese students and the way of application.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will be organized by the China overseas study
service center at the approval of the Ministry of Education. It is
aimed at promoting Sino-foreign exchanges in the field of
education and opening a new channel in training college students.
</P>
<P>
At present, more than 3 million students graduate from high
schools across China every year. However, institutes of higher
learning in the country enroll only 1 million freshmen annually,
falling far behind the demands, said an education official.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
