<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Frenchman Jackie Durand easily won
the sixth leg of the Paris-Nice cycling race on Friday, crossing
the line 38 seconds ahead of the pack.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old Durand finished the 211-kilometer stage between
Romans-sur-Isere to Sisteron in six hours 19 minutes and 20
seconds.
