<HEADLINE> Chinese Women Steal Limelight at All England Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BIRMINGHAM, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese women stole the
limelight of the All England Open Badminton Championships here on
Friday, taking three out of four seats on offer in the women's
singles semi-finals.
</P>
<P>
The only other place was grabbed by top seed Camilla Martin of
Denmark, who defeated Chinese rival Gong Ruina 11-3, 4-11 and 11-5
in a quarter-final match.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, shuttlers from Denmark and Indonesia dominated the
men's singles, sharing the places in the top four.
</P>
<P>
Gong Ruina, gold medalist from the Sweden Open last week, was
not match to Martin in the first set, surrendering at 11-3.
</P>
<P>
In the second set, the Chinese woman increased her attack and
had a complete control of the pace, levelling the score at one-all
with smashes and strokes.
</P>
<P>
Martin said after the match that she attributed failure in the
set to Gong Ruina's fast speed. "When I got used to it, I had
already lost it," she said.
</P>
<P>
In the third and final set, Martin played long rallies to Gong,
who, with weaker strength and power, had no chance to smash at the
net.
</P>
<P>
"I used long rallies to control Gong in the third set," Martin
said. "It proved right."
</P>
<P>
Martin will meet world champion Ye Zhaoying in the semi-final.
Ye, who lost to Martin in their recent meeting, defeated her
teammate Gong Zhichao 11-6 and 11-8 for the top four.
</P>
<P>
Another semi-final match will be held between second seed Dai
Yun and Zhou Mi. Dai, gold medal winner at the Chinese Taipei
Open earlier this year, met no challenge from Huang Chia-chi of
Chinese Taipei in the quarter-finals, winning the match at 11-5
and 11-4.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Mi, a slow starter, rallied from first set down to win the
match against joint fifth seed Mia Audina of Indonesia 7-11, 11-4
and 11-7.
</P>
<P>
While in the men's section, first seeded Peter gade Christensen
outplayed Johan Hadikusuma of Indonesia 17-15 and 15-8 to set up a
showdown with another Indonesian Budi Santoso in the semi-final.
Santoso overwhelmed his teammate Indra Wijaya 12-15, 15-11 and 15-
6.
</P>
<P>
The other semi-final match will also be an Indonesian-Dannish
duel, with joint ninth seed Taufik Hidayat taking on joint third
seed Poul-Erik Hoyer-Larsen.
</P>
<P>
The semi-final matches are slated for Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
