<HEADLINE> Malaysia Wants Continued Peacekeeping Efforts in Sierra Leone </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia has urged the
United Nations to ensure a continued and sustained peacekeeping
mission in Sierra Leone in order to help the West African country
to resolve its conflict.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia's Permanent Representative to the United Nations Hasmy
Agam has urged the international community to extend every
assistance and support to the peacekeeping efforts in Sierra Leone,
the Malaysian national news agency Bernama said Friday.
</P>
<P>
According to Bernama, Hasmy told a UN Security Council meeting
on the extension of mandate of the UN Observer Mission in Sierra
Leone that every effort should be made to ensure a continued
active involvement of UN peacekeepers and observers in Sierra
Leone.
</P>
<P>
He said the search for a political settlement in the war-torn
country must continue with undiminished support from the
international community.
</P>
<P>
He expressed Malaysia's concern at the "rapidly deteriorating
humanitarian situation" in Sierra Leone and urged that the safety
of persons engaged in humanitarian work there be ensured.
</P>
<P>
Hasmy also said Malaysia would urge for the strict compliance
with the provisions of existing arms embargoes imposed against the
country by the relevant Security Council resolutions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
