<HEADLINE> U.N.-Facilitated Intra-Afghan Talks Continues Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 12 (Xinhua) -- The second day of
intra-Afghan talks continued in Ashkabad, Turkmenistan, Friday in
a friendly, frank and focused way, a statement from the U.N.
Special Mission to Afghanistan said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued on behalf of the Afghan parties of the
Taleban and the opposition alliance known as the United Front,
said details of the discussions are confidential but the two sides
remain determined to work towards concrete results.
</P>
<P>
It said no time has been set for the overall duration of the
talks, which will resume Saturday morning following a round of
talks Friday evening.
</P>
<P>
The meeting is taking place under the auspices of the United
Nations and hosted by neighboring Turkmenistan. The talks are
based on the mutual willingness of both sides to search for a
political settlement through face-to-face negotiations.
</P>
<P>
The negotiations are the second round of direct talks between
the two parties to be held in Turkmenistan. 
