<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Host Regional Education Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 12 (Xinhua) -- A Zimbabwean minister said Friday
in Harare that more than 52 education ministers, technical staff
and other experts from Africa will attend an education conference
organized by the Organization of African Unity (OAU) next week.
</P>
<P>
The five-day conference which begins on March 15 in Harare,
capital of the southern African country, will focus on equity and
access to basic education for all, Higher Education and
Technology Minister, Ignstius Chombo, told reporters.
</P>
<P>
Chombo said that other areas to be discussed would be quality
and relevance of education and vocational training, capacity
building and support to informal education.
</P>
<P>
This conference follows the June 1996 OAU meeting in Yaounde,
Cameroon, where heads of state and governments dicussed education
in Africa. They adopted a resolution which proclaimed the period
1997 to 2006 the Decade of Education in Africa.
</P>
<P>
They also recommended the launching of the decade and the
convening of a pan-African ministerial conference to adopt the
program of action to be discussed next week.  
</P>
