<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Violinist Menuhin Dead in Berlin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bonn, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Yehudi Menuhin, the most brilliant
violinist of his generation, died Friday in Berlin at 82.
</P>
<P>
Menuhin, suffering a bout of feverish bronchitis, was admitted
to hospital where he died of heart failure. He had been planning
to conduct a concert and play works of Mendelssohn and Brahms in
Berlin.
</P>
<P>
German Federal President Roman Herzog mourned the loss of "one
of the most brilliant musicians of this century."
</P>
<P>
Menuhin, a New York born Russo-Jew, was acknowledged as a giant
in the field of music and an international personality who worked
tirelessly for humanitarian and the peace of world.
</P>
<P>
He was made a lord by Britain's Queen Elizabeth II, and became
a baron in year 1993.  
</P>
</TEXT>
