<HEADLINE> Lesotho Catholic Priests Instigated Coup Attempt: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 12 (Xinhua) -- Some Catholic priests
visited members of the Lesotho Defense Force at night in August
last year to persuade them to overthrow the army command and later
the government, a military intelligence report said.
</P>
<P>
The report was Friday submitted to a court martial in Maseru,
Lesotho's capital, by the commander of the Lesotho army,
Lieutenant-General Makhula Mosakeng, South African Press
Association (SAPA) said.
</P>
<P>
A group of 41 soldiers are appearing in a military court
charged with mutiny arising from events in Maseru in September
last year.
</P>
